	PERFORMING ARTS      April 14 at Swabhumi Urban Zone; 6 pm: Swabhumi is organising a musical evening to mark the Bengali New Year. Participants include Shibaji Chattopadhay, Shampa Kundu, Amrik Singh Arora, Swapan Bosu, Saikat Mitra, Thankamani Kutty amp; her troupe, and others. The show would be hosted by Pankaj Saha. This show would essentially deal with the New Year celebration in various provinces of our nation. Along with the cultural show, there would also be a food festival.     April 15 at Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture, 3 Regent Park; 10 am: A special cultural programme in memory of Krishna Chattopadhyay. Eminent singer and her disciple Nupurchhanda Ghosh will pay a musical tribute.     
	KERALA FESTIVAL      Till April 14 at Rabindra Sadan, Nandan-II, ICCR Art Gallery, Bangla Akademi, Gaganendra Pradarshashala: Government of Kerala, Cultural amp; departments along with different academies and Malayalee associations of Calcutta are organising Kolkata-Kerala Festival. Today at Rabindra Sadan, 5.30 pm: Concluding ceremony. Inauguration by chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee. Guest of honour: Sreenivasan, actor. Cultural programme: Dances based on Tagores works presented by Kalamandalam Calcutta, and drama Karnabharam presented by Manas, Calcutta.     n addition, exhibition of paintings, archive documents and books and Bangla Akademi, ICCR Art gallery and Gaganendra Pradarshashala.     
