	EXHIBITION      Till April 14 at South City Mall Atrium; 11 am - 8 pm: South City Mall is hosting Nature Bazaar to celebrate an eco-friendly Poila Baishakh. Artisans and handicraft-makers from villages across the country will showcase their products made from earthy and natural fibres along with major brands Mother Earth and Fabindia.     Till April 14 at Design, 108 Raja Basanta Roy Road, 4315; 11 am - 7.30 pm: Paramita Viswanathans special display of Resist printed sarees, silks and south Indian cottons.     Till April 14 at Green House, Tollygunge Metro station: Summer Surprise, an exhibition of latest summer wear, sarees, kurtis and suits.     Till April 14 at 16/2 Gariahat Road (opp. UCO Bank), 54718; 10.30 am - 8.30 pm: Joyitas Selection presents hand-embroidered sarees, dress materials, ladies and gents kurtas amp; kurtis, home linen, Lucknow chikan, tupperware, costume jewellery and gift items.     Till April 16 at Sasha shop, 27 Mirza Ghalib Street, 10 am - 7 pm: Garments and sarees in cool cottons and summer weaves.All those who wish events to be included in this column should write not less than a week ahead to: Time out, The Telegraph, 6 Prafulla Sarkar Street, Calcutta-700 001; Fax: 2234-8244     All those who wish events to be included in this column should write not less   than a week ahead to:   Time out, The Telegraph, 6, Prafulla Sarkar Street, Calcutta-700 001; 
